name: Juli's Thanksgiving Nachos
author: Juliana Hale
summary: These nachos give you the perfect mix of Tex-Mex and Thanksgiving flavors in every bite.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups shredded pepper Jack cheese
1 small bunch cilantro, coarsely chopped, or to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with foil; arrange chips on it
Stir turkey and salsa together in a bowl
Fill chips with turkey mixture, then top with cheese
Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and chips are golden, about 10 minutes
Meanwhile, stir cranberry sauce and lime juice together in a bowl
Top each chip with some of the cranberry-lime mixture and some of the sour cream
